history.content:
Data 8 is a hard pre-req for Data 100. You won't be allowed to enroll into Data 100 without meeting the pre-reqs of CS 61A, Data 8, and Math 54, unless there's a process I'm unaware of. Assuming you can't take Data 100, definitely enroll in Data 8 during Phase 1. All of the seats are reserved for freshmen and sophomores, and since you're planning on graduating next semester, you probably will be a senior at least. So Phase 1-ing Data 8 gives you the best chance of getting in the class even though you will be waitlisted.

You can also audit one of both of these classes, if you're so interested. The classes are large enough that no one would notice you in the class unenrolled.
